		<div id="comment_body_64945703">And yet, <a href="https://health.wusf.usf.edu/npr-health/2024-06-23/coronavirus-faq-is-the-6-foot-rule-debunked-or-does-distance-still-protect-you" title="usf.edu">it worked</a> [usf.edu] to slow the spread, just like wearing a mask.

<br> <br>

But let's ask this question. If someone is sick, are you standing a foot away from them as the talk and spew their spit on you, or do you keep your distance?

<br> <br>

But yeah, the guy who spent decades getting his medical degree, doing hardcore research, and treating thousands of people, did all that just to annoy people like you with a guess when trying to prevent you from dying.  How horrible.

<br> <br>

Perhaps you'd rather have JFK, Jr in charge who believes homeopathy and crystals will cure you and has contributed to the deaths of untold persons because he doesn't believe vaccines, any vaccine, protect you.</div>
	</div>

